{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Using raw source code as the inputTraditional manually crafted features in source code analysis tend to be syntax-based, disregarding the valuable semantic information embedded in the code.",
    "To overcome this limitation, Chen et al. [328] introduced a novel technique that visualizes the source code of programs as images and then employs CNN to extract image features.",
    "These extracted features are utilized for building more effective defect prediction models.",
    "Uddin et al. [343] leveraged Bi-LSTM to capture expressive features from the embedded token vectors obtained through BERT applied to the source code.",
    "This technique allows effectively harnessing the semantic information within the code for defect prediction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To overcome this limitation, Chen et al. [328] introduced a novel technique that visualizes the source code of programs as images and then employs CNN to extract image features.",
    "Uddin et al. [343] leveraged Bi-LSTM to capture expressive features from the embedded token vectors obtained through BERT applied to the source code."
  ]
}